## Selected Outputs

### Adjusted odds ratios for good self-reported health

This model examines whether safety-net receipt, income after migration, and clinic access predict good self-reported health. Clinic access emerges as the strongest positive predictor, while safety-net receipt does not independently predict good health after adjustment.

![Adjusted odds ratios for good self-reported health](outputs/figures/HYpo%201%3A%20ODDS%20ratio.jpeg)

---

### Employment improvement by safety-net receipt

This figure shows the relationship between safety-net receipt and employment improvement after migration. It supports the finding that safety nets are more strongly associated with livelihood transitions than with direct health improvements.

![Employment improvement by safety-net receipt](outputs/figures/Hypo%202%3A%20Employment%20graph.jpeg)

